      "writtenOn": "2019-05-10T13:08:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ok. I initial thought it would be no problem because the two different recs will be created on either side of the ShouldDrawAsPath calculation. But, MakeRecAndEffects uses sk_relax on some matrix entries. This could cause problem by having inputs that would be on either side of the ShouldDrawAsPath create the same rec. I will talk to Ben about ways of handling this. We could just remove the sk_relax, or add a bit to the key that indicates path. At this point, I think the chances of this aliasing are very small.",
